original:
Biological data refers to information derived from living organisms and their products. This can include medicinal compounds such as serums and vaccines. Compared to other forms of data, biological data is notably complex and multifaceted. It encompasses various types, including textual information, sequence data, protein structures, genomic data, and amino acids, among others.
